properties.areaDesc: Croatan and Roanoke Sounds; Alligator River; Pamlico and Pungo Rivers; Neuse and Bay Rivers; Pamlico Sound; Albemarle Sound
properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 12 at 10:10PM EST until January 13 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Newport/Morehead City NC
properties.description:
...HIGH SEAS WILL CONTINUE THROUGH EARLY WEDNESDAY MORNING...
...DENSE SEA FOG CONTINUES INTO MONDAY AFTERNOON...

.Elevated seas will linger across the waters into early Wednesday
morning. Sea fog will be dense at times into Monday afternoon,
and may continue to plague marine areas through mid week as warm
and humid southwest winds continue to blow over the relatively cool
waters.

* WHAT...Dense fog will reduce visibility to less than one
nautical mile.

* WHERE...Portions of Albemarle, Croatan and Roanoke and Pamlico
Sounds and Alligator, Neuse and Bay and Pamlico and Pungo
Rivers.

* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 1 PM EST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Low visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM EST MONDAY
